snippet.textDisplay:
Song Name: Lagi Bina Chal Mele Noon Challiye, 
Artists: Saieen Zahoor & Sanam Marvi,
Album Name: Episode 6, 
Coke Studio Season 9,
Music Director: Jaffer Zaidi


===Lyrics=====

Laali mere laal ki
Jit dekhoon tit laal
Laal vekhan main gayi
Main vi hoi laal,

(Everywhere I turn, I see the brilliant colour of my beloved I went to see that dazzling hue And myself got dyed in his blessed colour).

Kesariya balma aawo ni
padhaaro Maare des.
Rain na jaage
Jaage na rain na jaage (x2),

Ho lagi bina
rain na jaage koi (x2).

(My handsome beloved, come to me Come home to me please No one stays up all night No one stays up all through the night Without the yearning of love, no one stays up all night in prayer)

Oho jaage jis nu aap jagave
Arey hor na jaage koi
Ho laggi bina
rain na jaage koi. 


(Only he stays awake whose inner yearning keeps him awake No one else stays awake Without the yearning of love, no one stays up all night in prayer)

Ho pehla pehar
har koi jaage (x2),
Par duja na jaage koi
Ho laggi bina
rain na jaage koi.


(Everyone can stay up for some of the night But no one devotes all the long night to prayer Without the yearning of love, no one stays up all night in prayer)

Ho jeewein ho bulleya oye
Mela ae pal di pal eh
Chal mele nu chaliye
O aakhir jaana mar ve
Chal mele nu chaliye.

(O Bulle Shah live long The sparkling assembly of the world is now here and now gone Let’s go and see its sights for these few moments We must ultimately die and leave here Let’s go and see its sights for these few moments)

Ho mela pal di pal ve
Chal mele noon challiye
Ho aakhir jana e ghar ve
Chal mele noon challiye.

O pehla mela
allah kita
Haye malkaan vekh te
sajda ve kita,

(God gathered the first assembly On his order, the angels bowed to Adam)

Jeda vekh ke gaya darr ve
Chal mele nu chaliye
Ho aakhre jana ghar ve
Chal mere nu chaliye,

Rain na jaage
Jaage na rain na jaage (x4),

Ho dukhi jaage
dukh de kaaran (x2),
Par sukhi na jaage koi
Ho lagi bina
rain na jaage koi (x2).

(It is sorrows that keep the sorrowful awake But the joyful are not kept awake Without the yearning of love, no one stays up all night in prayer.)

Bulla eh peer manawe
Te darshan yaar da paave (x2),

Nach ke oh peer manawe
Te darshan yaar da paave,

(Bulleh Shah cajoles his guide And is thus blessed with his beloved’s sight He dances to cajole his guide And is thus blessed with his beloved’s sight)

Bulla eh peer manawe
Te darshan yaar da paave (loop),
(O allah, Allah)
Nach ke oh peer manaanda
Te darshan yaar da paanda (x2),

O lagi bina
rain na jaage koi (x2).
